{"questionId":"14415055","questionHtml":"<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AD</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use distance formula for points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>DA</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>11</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (miles) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0384</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msqrt><mn>170</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn></math> miles. Award<em><strong> M0A0</strong></em> for finding the equation of the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>DA</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>DA</mi></math>&nbsp;may be seen in part (b) but this should not be accepted as answer for part (a).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14415055","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find AD.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}